Presenting– another kuluring kala core product ✨floral mirror✨
A short story behind this product- A client approached me asking for a resin wall art; something that can act as a decor piece as well as can be put to use, and I had to take that challenge (more of an opportunity). After a lot of discussion, where I sent him sketches and ideas, I finally came up with this product– FLORAL MIRROR– that I am extremely proud of (knowing that I haven’t seen anyone’s made this product, which also explains why is it a kuluring kala core product). I have to say, he trusted me with this product and asked me to not worry and just do my thing when I was a little concerned about how will resin react on mirror. There were some ups and downs during the making process, ngl, but this was one of the coolest experiment till date. And the hustle was worth all of it as soon as the saw the final product. 
I realised how clients can be your biggest motivation✨
Thanks for trusting me with this @jainamshhah 😇
.

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s something random -
UV resin is not as easy as it seemed. It has its own perks but can totally go against your requirements, given how fast it dries (not even exaggerating it dried within a min!) Learning process isn’t only about creating new but also about making mistakes and getting better at every attempt. I believe, it’s the most low-key feeling of achievement, when one only chooses to look at the failure as a fall back and conveniently ignores how failing is an important part in the process of the achievement. Anywho, moral of the story is I am finally getting better it, and I am loving uv resin ever since; realised how I kept feeling disappointed with every time uv resin didn’t work for me, only to realise how it was a massive step towards getting better🌻
So keep trying and do not stop! That was all in my today’s random gyaan. 🥰
.
.
.
